A is for Awesome like this podcast” is a weekly podcast from comedian YAASEEN BARNES and writer KAREN JEYNES, where they share interesting facts and stories, and inject a little positivity and entertainment into your day. If you want to know which world record Zimbabwe recently claimed, why babies only blink twice a minute, or why frogs say “ribbit”, this is a podcast for you. Join them on their quest to discover the awesome which is all around us. Introducing “A is for awesome like this podcast”, brought to you by the overcrowded brains of Yaaseen Barnes and Karen Jeynes. In this episode we explain what the hell we were thinking when we started this podcast, discuss a world record that Zimbabwe recently snatched back from Australia, and hear what Owen Wilson would sound like if he was Yaaseen Barnes.  Catchy jingle by Godfrey Johnson. New doses available every Wednesday. Follow us on Twitter: @ya_a_seen_him and @karenjeynes.